[DEEP] Final diagnosis:
The build fails because `%pyproject_wheel` calls `/usr/bin/python3.13 -mpip wheel`, but `pip` is not installed in the system Python 3.13 by default in SUSE Tumbleweed builds. The spec needs an explicit BuildRequires for pip (or use `%{python_module python-pip}` if available).

Run this to check what pip packages are available:

```
rpmbuild -bi --short-circuit /home/abuild/rpmbuild/SOURCES/oterm.spec 2>&1 | grep -i pip
```

Then add `BuildRequires: %{python_module python-pip}` (or the appropriate SUSE-provided pip package) to fix the `%pyproject_wheel` call.

